ItemDef.Name: EXC11
ItemDef.def:Label: Have type 1 diabetes as suggested by positive anti-glutamate decarboxylase (GAD) and/or anti-islet cell antibody, or history of ketoacidosis, or any other type of diabetes, other than type 2.

ItemDef.Name: EXC12
ItemDef.def:Label: Are taking any glucose-lowering oral agents other than metformin within 3 months prior to Visit 1.

ItemDef.Name: EXC13
ItemDef.def:Label: GLP-1 analog or incretin mimetic w/in 6 mon prior to Visit 1, insulin therapy ever for diabetes. if insulin for short-term management of acute conditions > 3 mon prior to visit 1 may participate.

ItemDef.Name: EXC14
ItemDef.def:Label: Are currently taking prescription or over-the-counter medications to promote weight loss.

ItemDef.Name: EXC15
ItemDef.def:Label: Receiving chronic systemic glucocorticoid therapy (excluding topical, intraocular, intranasal, intra-articular, or inhaled preparations) or received such therapy within 4 weeks prior to Visit 1.

ItemDef.Name: EXC16
ItemDef.def:Label: Have a known clinically significant gastric emptying abnormality, have undergone gastric bypass (bariatric) surgery, or chronically take drugs that directly reduce gastrointestinal motility.

ItemDef.Name: EXC17
ItemDef.def:Label: Are currently taking a central nervous system stimulant (for example, Ritalin-SR).

ItemDef.Name: EXC18
ItemDef.def:Label: Any of following <= 6 months prior to Visit 1: ACS, CHD treated by CABG or PCI, heart failure, atrial or ventricular arrhythmia, pacemaker implant, cs signs of ischemic heart disease, tia or stroke.

ItemDef.Name: EXC19
ItemDef.def:Label: Poorly controlled hypertension at Visits 1 or 4, or change antihypertensive meds between Visits 1 and 4, renal artery stenosis, or evidence of labile BP including symptomatic postural hypotension.

ItemDef.Name: EXC20
ItemDef.def:Label: Visit 1 ECG on, relevant for interpretation or indicates cardiac disease (QTc [Bazett] int >450 msec males or >470 msec females); and aberrant, blocked, or impaired propagation (pr int >220 msec).

ItemDef.Name: EXC21
ItemDef.def:Label: Have obvious clinical signs or symptoms of liver disease, acute or chronic hepatitis, or ALT levels >3.0 times the upper limit of the reference range at Visit 1, determined by central lab.

ItemDef.Name: EXC22
ItemDef.def:Label: Have obvious clinical signs or symptoms of pancreatitis (section 6.2.1.1.1), a history of chronic pancreatitis or acute pancreatitis at Visit 1 , as determined by the investigator.

ItemDef.Name: EXC22A
ItemDef.def:Label: Signs or symptoms of pancreatitis, history of chronic or acute pancreatitis at Visit 1. excluded if amylase >=3 times ULN and/or lipase >=2 times ULN, as determined by the central lab at Visit 1.

ItemDef.Name: EXC23
ItemDef.def:Label: Have a serum creatinine >=1.5 mg/dl for men or >=1.4 mg/dl for women, or a creatinine clearance <60 ml/minute as determined by the central laboratory at Visit 1.

ItemDef.Name: EXC24
ItemDef.def:Label: Have uncontrolled diabetes defined as 2 or more episodes of hyperosmolar state requiring hospitalization in the 6 months prior to Visit 1.

ItemDef.Name: EXC25
ItemDef.def:Label: Have evidence of a significant active, uncontrolled endocrine or autoimmune abnormality, as judged by the screening investigator.

ItemDef.Name: EXC26
ItemDef.def:Label: Have a history of a transplanted organ (corneal transplants [keratoplasty] allowed).

ItemDef.Name: EXC27
ItemDef.def:Label: Have active or untreated malignancy or in remission from clin sig malignancy other than basal or squamous cell skin cancer, in situ carcinoma of the cervix or in situ prostate cancer < 5 years.

ItemDef.Name: EXC28
ItemDef.def:Label: Have any other condition (such as known drug or alcohol abuse or psychiatric disorder), in the opinion of the investigator, that may preclude the patient from following and completing the protocol.

ItemDef.Name: EXC29
ItemDef.def:Label: Are investigator site personnel directly affiliated with this study and/or their immediate families. immediate family is defined as a spouse, parent, child, or sibling, whether biological or adopted.

ItemDef.Name: EXC31
ItemDef.def:Label: Have received treatment within the last 30 days with a drug that has not received regulatory approval in the respective country for any indication at the time of study entry.

ItemDef.Name: EXC32
ItemDef.def:Label: Have participated in an interventional medical, surgical, or pharmaceutical study (a study in which a medical or surgical treatment was given) within 30 days prior to entry into the study.

ItemDef.Name: EXC33
ItemDef.def:Label: Have previously completed or withdrawn from this study after providing informed consent.

ItemDef.Name: INC1
ItemDef.def:Label: Have type 2 diabetes based on the disease diagnostic criteria (World Health Organization [WHO] classification, protocol attachment GBCK.3).

ItemDef.Name: INC10
ItemDef.def:Label: Have given written informed consent to participate in this study in accordance with local regulations and the ethical review board (ERB) governing the study site.

ItemDef.Name: INC2
ItemDef.def:Label: Are antihyperglycemic medication-nave (diet and exercise only) or are taking metformin as monotherapy and are willing to discontinue this medication.

ItemDef.Name: INC3
ItemDef.def:Label: Have completed at least 8 weeks of wash-out prior to randomization (Visit 4), if taking metformin prior to Visit2.

ItemDef.Name: INC3A
ItemDef.def:Label: Have completed at least 8 weeks of wash-out prior to collecting the hba1c sample for randomization (Visit 4), if taking metformin prior to Visit 2.

ItemDef.Name: INC4
ItemDef.def:Label: HbA1c, from central lab, Visit 1 and 4. therapy at Visit 1 HbA1c at Visit 1 HbA1c at Visit 4 diet and exercise >=7.0% to <=9.5% >=7.0% to <=9.5% metformin monotherapy >=6.0% to <=8.5% >=7.0% to <=9.5%

ItemDef.Name: INC4A
ItemDef.def:Label: HbA1c, from central lab, Visit 1 and 4. therapy at Visit 1 HbA1c, at Visit 1 HbA1c, at Visit 4 diet and exercise >=7.0% to <=9.5% >=6.5% to <=9.5% metformin monotherapy >=6.5% to <=9.0% >=6.5% to <=9.

ItemDef.Name: INC5
ItemDef.def:Label: Men or women who are between the ages of 18 to 75 years, inclusive.

ItemDef.Name: INC6
ItemDef.def:Label: Females of childbearing potential must test negative for pregnancy at Visit 1, agree to use a reliable method of birth control during and 1 month following last dose and not be breastfeeding.

ItemDef.Name: INC7
ItemDef.def:Label: BMI between 23 and 40 kg/m2, inclusive, for patients who are native to, and reside in, south and/or east Asia. all other patients must have a BMI between 27 and 40 kg/m2, inclusive.

ItemDef.Name: INC7A
ItemDef.def:Label: BMI between 23 and 40 kg/m2, inclusive, for patients who are native to, and reside in, south and/or east Asia. all other patients must have a BMI between 25 and 40 kg/m2, inclusive.

ItemDef.Name: INC8
ItemDef.def:Label: Have a stable weight during the 3 months prior to Visit 1, in the opinion of the investigator.

ItemDef.Name: INC9
ItemDef.def:Label: Motivated, capable, willing to perform smg testing, self-inject treatment, (if not able to perform the injections must have assistance from persons trained to inject drug) and maintain a study diary.
